Subject: [liste-egc] Permanent Assistant Professor position - University of
 Tours, France

The Department of Computer Science (http://www.info.univ-tours.fr/dp/en) 
at the faculty of Sciences & Technologies at the university of Tours 
(http://www.univ-tours.fr/) invites applications for a permanent 
Assistant Professor (Maitre de Conferences) position, starting in 
September 2014 in the nice city of Blois (http://en.blois.fr/)located in 
the Unesco World Heritage area of the "Loire valley".

Applicants must hold a PhD degree in Computer Science and have one or 
two years of teaching and research experience in the fields of data 
management, web technologies or business intelligence. The applicant is 
expected to teach undergraduate and graduate courses, in particular in 
the Erasmus Mundus IT4BI Master 
(http://it4bi.univ-tours.fr/).Nevertheless, this position involves 
teaching in French too, hence proficiency in this language is also 
expected in the short term.

The selected applicant will join the research team BdTln (databases and 
natural language processing) 
(http://www.info.univ-tours.fr/dp/sites/default/files/storage/teacher/2013-05-22-BdTln-IT4BI-1.pdf) 
of the LI (Laboratoire d’Informatique EA6300 - 
http://li.univ-tours.fr/). Relevant research topics include natural 
language processing, OLAP and datamining, web data management and 
interoperability.

Several projects offer PhD and Master supervision opportunities dealing 
with, for instance, multi-word expressions (PARSEME 
http://www.parseme.eu), or Open Data analytics (DOPAN 
http://www.info.univ-tours.fr/dp/fr/recherche/dopan), or semantic web 
mediation (recent regional project IPat - Intelligence des patrimoines - 
led by the CESR http://cesr.univ-tours.fr/).

If more information is needed on research topics please contact Arnaud 
Giacometti (arnaud.giacometti@univ-tours.fr 
<mailto:arnaud.giacometti@univ-tours.fr>) for datamining and OLAP, 
Béatrice Bouchou Markhoff (beatrice.bouchou@univ-tours.fr 
<mailto:beatrice.bouchou@univ-tours.fr>) for web data management and 
Jean-Yves Antoine (jean-yves.antoine@univ-tours.fr 
<mailto:jean-yves.antoine@univ-tours.fr>) for NLP.

If more information is needed on teaching tasks, all of the above 
contacts can answer too, being all involved in the concerned programs.

A "qualification aux fonctions de Maître de Conférences" certificate 
from the french "Conseil national des universités" 
(http://cnu27.iut2.upmf-grenoble.fr/) is usually required to apply. 
However candidates who already hold an Assistant Professor (or 
equivalent) position in a higher education institution outside France, 
may be exempted from this certificate.

Important dates:

March 2014: Complete application submission

May 16th 2014: Interviews by selection committee

Late June 2014: Notification to candidates

September 1st 2014: Position starting

